<p><i><b>Fatherland</b></i> is a bestselling 1992 <a href="/wiki/Thriller_(genre)" title="Thriller (genre)">thriller</a> <a href="/wiki/Novel" title="Novel">novel</a> by the <a href="/wiki/England" title="England">English</a> <a href="/wiki/Writer" title="Writer">writer</a> and <a href="/wiki/Journalism" title="Journalism">journalist</a> <a href="/wiki/Robert_Harris_(novelist)" title="Robert Harris (novelist)">Robert Harris</a>, which doubles as a work of <a href="/wiki/Alternate_history_(fiction)" title="Alternate history (fiction)" class="mw-redirect">alternate history</a>. The novel is based on the premise of a world in which <a href="/wiki/Nazi_Germany" title="Nazi Germany">Nazi Germany</a> was triumphant in <a href="/wiki/World_War_II" title="World War II">World War II</a>.</p>
